    <introduction>
        <paragraph>This document outlines a pre-ride inspection checklist for a bicycle. The checklist covers various components, including brakes, tires, wheels, headset, chain, handlebar, and computer.</paragraph>
    </introduction>
    <preRideInspectionChecklist>
        <brakes>
            <item>
                <title>Pads</title>
                <steps>
                    <step>Check pad width</step>
                    <step>Check pad clearance</step>
                </steps>
            </item>
            <item>
                <title>Callipers</title>
                <steps>
                    <step>Ensure link wire is firmly attached</step>
                </steps>
            </item>
            <item>
                <title>Levers</title>
                <steps>
                    <step>Check for approximately 1 inch of travel before engagement</step>
                    <step>Check for space between lever and handlebar when fully pulled</step>
                </steps>
            </item>
            <item>
                <title>Cables</title>
                <steps>
                    <step>Inspect for cuts or fraying</step>
                </steps>
            </item>
        </brakes>
        <tires>
            <item>
                <title>Pressure</title>
                <table>
                    <row>
                        <terrain>Off Road</terrain>
                        <minPressure>35 lbs</minPressure>
                        <maxPressure>40 lbs</maxPressure>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <terrain>On Road</terrain>
                        <minPressure>55 lbs</minPressure>
                        <maxPressure>60 lbs</maxPressure>
                    </row>
                </table>
            </item>
            <item>
                <title>Condition</title>
                <steps>
                    <step>Check for cracks or splits</step>
                </steps>
            </item>
        </tires>
        <wheels>
            <item>
                <title>Bearings</title>
                <steps>
                    <step>Ensure bearings are not loose</step>
                </steps>
            </item>
            <item>
                <title>Trueness</title>
                <steps>
                    <step>Check if the wheel is true</step>
                </steps>
            </item>
            <item>
                <title>Spokes</title>
                <steps>
                    <step>Check for broken spokes</step>
                    <step>If spokes are not broken, ensure they are tight</step>
                </steps>
            </item>
            <item>
                <title>Axel Nuts</title>
                <steps>
                    <step>Ensure axel nuts are tight</step>
                </steps>
            </item>
        </wheels>
        <headset>
            <item>
                <title>Bearing Tightness</title>
                <steps>
                    <step>Ensure headset bearings are tight</step>
                </steps>
            </item>
        </headset>
        <chain>
            <item>
                <title>Link Movement</title>
                <steps>
                    <step>Check for easy movement of links</step>
                </steps>
            </item>
        </chain>
        <handlebar>
            <item>
                <title>Stem Condition</title>
                <steps>
                    <step>Do not ride with a cracked stem</step>
                    <step>If the stem is loose, tighten it</step>
                </steps>
            </item>
            <item>
                <title>Handlebar Twist</title>
                <steps>
                    <step>If handlebars twist in stem, tighten clamp bolt</step>
                </steps>
            </item>
        </handlebar>
        <computer>
            <item>
                <title>Display</title>
                <steps>
                    <step>Check computer display for speed and distance readings</step>
                </steps>
            </item>
        </computer>
    </preRideInspectionChecklist>
    <exampleUseCase>
        <paragraph>To perform a pre-ride inspection, follow these steps:</paragraph>
        <steps>
            <step>Start with the brakes: check pads, callipers, levers, and cables.</step>
            <step>Move on to tires: check pressure and condition.</step>
            <step>Inspect wheels: bearings, trueness, spokes, and axel nuts.</step>
            <step>Check headset bearing tightness.</step>
            <step>Verify chain link movement.</step>
            <step>Examine handlebar stem condition and tighten if necessary.</step>
            <step>Finally, check computer display for speed and distance readings.</step>
        </steps>
        <paragraph>By following this checklist, you can ensure your bicycle is in good working condition before heading out on a ride.</paragraph>
    </exampleUseCase>
